{
  "texts": [
    "A comprehensive history, in our opinion, needs to be composed by someone at some point.",
    "Part of the challenge is the need for the brave author who takes this project to be fluent in at least both ancient Greek and German.",
    "The former language is key because Aristotle can be viewed as the primogenitor (e.g., see",
    "Topica and De Sophisticis Elenchis in his Organon, available in McKeon,).",
    "German is crucial because, even to this day, the remarkable work of Lorenzen, momentarily discussed, has not been fully translated from the German."
  ]
}